parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To carry, bear away (sometimes with violence). From apo and phero; to bear off.
In, on, among. A primary preposition denoting position, and instrumentality, i.e. A relation of rest; 'in, ' at, on, by, etc.
Wind, breath, spirit.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
A mountain, hill. Probably from an obsolete oro; a mountain: -hill, mount(-ain).
Large, great, in the widest sense.
And, even, also, namely.
High, lofty. From hupsos; lofty.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolonged form of an obsolete primary of the same meaning; to show.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Dative 1st Person Singular
str2: I, the first-person pronoun. A primary pronoun of the first person I.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
Set apart by (or for) God, holy, sacred. From hagos; sacred.
A city, the inhabitants of a city. Probably from the same as polemos, or perhaps from polus; a town.
Of Hebrew origin; Hierusalem, the capitol of Palestine.

parse: Verb - Present Participle Active - Accusative Feminine Singular
str2: To go down, come down, either from the sky or from higher land, descend. From kata and the base of basis; to descend.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
Perhaps from the same as oros; the sky; by extension, heaven; by implication, happiness, power, eternity; specially, the Gospel.
From, away from. A primary particle; 'off, ' i.e. Away, in various senses.
A deity, especially the supreme Divinity; figuratively, a magistrate; by Hebraism, very.
